track_notes: This track follows a quad track up to the base of the mountain where it ends.  From there it is a bushwhack to the summit.  This track will avoid a bump before the summit by contouring around the side but generally just go uphill until there is no more uphill left.  I crossed several places where what seemed to be a motorcycle trail so some closer investigation in the summer time could expose a better route.  Reliable cell phone reception was available at the summit.

This track will take advantage of existing roads and trails, minimizing the bushwhacking and improving the enjoyment of this summit.  This portion of the Forestry Trunk Road is maintained all year, making this summit great for summer, shoulder seasons and winter.  Start at the drainage and follow the drainage up using well trodden game trails until you meet a quad track, follow the quad track until you meet an old logging road.  Follow the logging road through an open clear-cut area to the summit ridge.  At this point you will look for a motorcycle track on the top of the ridge.  Follow the motorcycle track to the summit.  Cell phone service is available at the summit.

After trying three different tracks, this one trumps them all by avoiding all the bushwhacking.  It avoids the misery-infused willow bushwhack on the next best option.  Although there will be a 40 meter elevation loss on the ascent, it will be worth it to follow cut-lines and trails the entire distance.
